Definitions/Abbreviations

General

  • M: Matches, including finals matches
  • W: Wins
  • L: Losses
  • D: Draws
  • For: Total points scored
  • Avg: Average points scored
  • Acc: Accuracy (goals / scoring shots)
  • Against: Total points conceded
  • Avg: Average points conceded
  • Acc: Opposition accuracy
  • %: Points scored / points conceded
  • Points: Wins × 4 + Draws × 2
  • MR: Points / (Matches × 4)
  • Ladder: Ladder position at the end of the home & away season
  • Teams: Total teams competing in the league in the particular year

Overall Season Rating

Overall season rating is an attempt to rate each team in a given season. Only matches played during the season are considered in these calculations. Rating takes into account opponent strength and venue advantage/disadvantage.

In addition, ratings are calculated from adjusted scores which are a weighted average of a team’s actual score and their score had they kicked at an expected accuracy. The expected accuracy is a weighted average of the competition-wide accuracy and the team’s accuracy in the current season.

  • Rating: Estimated points above or below an average team for the given season.
  • Relative Rating: Standardised rating (Rating / standard deviation of all ratings for the given season.)
  • Attack: Estimated points scored above or below an average team for the given season.
  • Relative Attack: Standardised attack rating
  • Defense: Estimated points conceded above or below an average team for the given season.
  • Relative Defense: Standardised defensive rating
  • Adjusted %: (Competition Average Score + Attack Rating) / (Competition Average Score - Defense Rating) × 100
  • Adjusted Rating: Square root of the absolute value of (Adjusted % / 100 - 1) × Relative Rating, multiplied by the sign of the overall team rating.

Rating at End of Season

End-of-season ratings are an estimate of a team’s rating after the last match of the season, which will be weighted toward the latest results in the given season.
